gomodel:SYNGO_588  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: By immunoelectron microscopy eIF-4E immunoreactivity was revealed to be localized to the postsynaptic sites, especially to the microvesicle-like structures underneath the postsynaptic membrane in the spine, some of which were localized in close proximity to PSD of type 1 synapses.. Experimental description: In brief, brains from Wistar rats (males, 6 weeks old), page 170" ;
